OL,3,CRichard Holden's exit from region he
OL,4,Cclaimed to be 'bloody loyal' to
OL,6,FMr Holden argued he had "already
OL,7,Fanswered" questions over his selection
OL,8,Fin the Channel 4 News interview, while
OL,9,Fan aide of his, standing just off-
OL,10,Fcamera (as is normal), said
OL,11,Fbroadcasters had agreed the interview
OL,12,Fwould be about class sizes.
OL,14,FSky News' Jon Craig, conducting the
OL,15,Finterview, insisted he could ask about
OL,16,Fwhatever he (and other broadcasters
OL,17,Fwho had put forward questions) wanted.
OL,19,FIt was a very unusual on-camera row,
OL,20,Fand a difficult situation for the
OL,21,FConservatives.
